cmIPMIB.name: cmIPMIB

revisions.description: Notes from release 201407180000Z, (1) Added new IpManagementTunnelType literals: - gcc0based, - gcc1based, - gcc2based. Notes from release 201012080000Z, (1)Added cmIpManagementTrafficBridgingSecurityEnabled scalar for the Bridged Management LAN feature on GE20x devices for Release 5.1CC. Notes from release 201010230000Z, (1)Added cmIpManagementTrafficBridgingEnabled scalar for the Bridged Management LAN feature on GE20x devices for Release 5.1CC. Notes from release 200904200000Z, (1)MIB version ready for release FSP150CC 4.1. (a)Added new table IpManagementTunnel (b)Added attribute cmIpInterfaceRIPv2Enabled (c)Added attribute cmARPEntryType (d)Added attribute cmStaticRouteInterface, cmStaticRouteAdvertise Notes from release 200803030000Z, (1)MIB version ready for release FSP150CM 3.1.

cmIPMIB.contactinfo: Raghav Trivedi ADVA Optical Networking, Inc. Tel: +1 972 759-1239 E-mail: rtrivedi@advaoptical.com Postal: 2301 N. Greenville Ave. #300 Richardson, TX USA 75082
cmIPMIB.description: This module defines the IP MIB definitions used by the F3 (FSP150CM/CC) product lines. Copyright (C) ADVA Optical Networking.

CmDhcpRole.name: CmDhcpRole
CmDhcpRole.description: DHCP role when DHCP is enabled on an interface.

cmIpFlushARPCacheAction.name: cmIpFlushARPCacheAction
cmIpFlushARPCacheAction.description: This object allows user to initiate Flush ARP action.

cmIpProxyARPEnabled.name: cmIpProxyARPEnabled
cmIpProxyARPEnabled.description: This object allows user to enable/disable Proxy ARP.

cmIpPingDestination.name: cmIpPingDestination
cmIpPingDestination.description: This object allows user to specify the IP Address to which ICMP Ping will be initiated.

cmIpInitiatePingAction.name: cmIpInitiatePingAction
cmIpInitiatePingAction.description: This object allows user to initiate ICMP Ping on cmIpPingDestination.

cmIpPingResult.name: cmIpPingResult
cmIpPingResult.description: This object provides the results of a previous ICMP Ping Action.

cmIpTraceRouteDestination.name: cmIpTraceRouteDestination
cmIpTraceRouteDestination.description: This object allows user to specify the IP Address to which Trace Route will be initiated.

cmIpInitiateTraceRouteAction.name: cmIpInitiateTraceRouteAction
cmIpInitiateTraceRouteAction.description: This object allows user to initiate TraceRoute on cmIpTraceRouteDestination.

cmIpTraceRouteResult.name: cmIpTraceRouteResult
cmIpTraceRouteResult.description: This object provides the results of a previous TraceRoute Action.

cmIpManagementTrafficBridgingEnabled.name: cmIpManagementTrafficBridgingEnabled
cmIpManagementTrafficBridgingEnabled.description: This object allows the user to control the IP Management Traffic Bridging feature. When enabled, the system is managed using the IP address specified at the Management LAN port. All IP packets that are not terminated at the node will be bridged over the Management LAN.

cmIpManagementTrafficBridgingSecurityEna.name: cmIpManagementTrafficBridgingSecurityEnabled
cmIpManagementTrafficBridgingSecurityEna.description: This object allows the user to control the IP Management Traffic Bridging feature's security. When enables, the system supports a secure Management Traffic Bridge.

cmIpv6PingInterface.name: cmIpv6PingInterface
cmIpv6PingInterface.description: This object allows user to specify the IPV6 Address related interface.

cmIpv6PingDestination.name: cmIpv6PingDestination
cmIpv6PingDestination.description: This object allows user to specify the IPV6 Address to which ICMP Ping will be initiated.

cmIpv6InitiatePingAction.name: cmIpv6InitiatePingAction
cmIpv6InitiatePingAction.description: This object allows user to initiate ICMP Ping on cmIpv6PingDestination.

cmIpv6TraceRouteDestination.name: cmIpv6TraceRouteDestination
cmIpv6TraceRouteDestination.description: This object allows user to specify the IPV6 Address to which Trace Route will be initiated.

cmIpv6InitiateTraceRouteAction.name: cmIpv6InitiateTraceRouteAction
cmIpv6InitiateTraceRouteAction.description: This object allows user to initiate TraceRoute on cmIpv6TraceRouteDestination.

cmIpv6ProxyNDPEnabled.name: cmIpv6ProxyNDPEnabled
cmIpv6ProxyNDPEnabled.description: This object whether enabled proxy NDP.

cmIpv6FwdEnabled.name: cmIpv6FwdEnabled
cmIpv6FwdEnabled.description: This object whether NE works in router mode or host mode. Forwarding enable:router mode, forwarding disable: host mode.

cmIpFlushNDPCacheAction.name: cmIpFlushNDPCacheAction
cmIpFlushNDPCacheAction.description: This object allows user to initiate Flush NDP action.

cmIpPtpArpRtrvAction.name: cmIpPtpArpRtrvAction
cmIpPtpArpRtrvAction.description: If user want to get PTP arp from cmARPEntry, user need to configure this object first.

cmIpManagementTrafficDscpEnabled.name: cmIpManagementTrafficDscpEnabled
cmIpManagementTrafficDscpEnabled.description: This object controls whether the DSCP value is modified for the transmitted management traffic whether it is locally generated or routed.

cmIpManagementTrafficDscp.name: cmIpManagementTrafficDscp
cmIpManagementTrafficDscp.description: This object specifies the DSCP value and it is applicable when cmIpManagementTrafficDscpEnabled is enabled.

cmIpSNMPv1InterfaceName.name: cmIpSNMPv1InterfaceName
cmIpSNMPv1InterfaceName.description: This object allows the user to specify the IP interface name, which will be used in the SNMPv1 TRAP PDUs as the Agent's IP Address.

cmIpSourceAddressType.name: cmIpSourceAddressType
cmIpSourceAddressType.description: This object allows the user to specify whether the System IP Address or the Outgoing IP Interface's Address should be used in outgoing IP PDUs.

cmIpSourceAddressInterfaceName.name: cmIpSourceAddressInterfaceName
cmIpSourceAddressInterfaceName.description: This object allows the user to specify the IP interface name when cmIpSourceAddressType is 'systemipaddr'. The IP Address associated with the IP interface name is set as the source IP Address in outgoing PDUs.

cmIpInterfaceDhcpEnabled.name: cmIpInterfaceDhcpEnabled
cmIpInterfaceDhcpEnabled.description: Whether or not DHCP is enabled on this interface.

cmIpInterfaceDhcpRole.name: cmIpInterfaceDhcpRole
cmIpInterfaceDhcpRole.description: Specify the DHCP role on this interface.

cmIpInterfacePhysicalAddress.name: cmIpInterfacePhysicalAddress
cmIpInterfacePhysicalAddress.description: Physical Address associated with the IP Address.

cmIpInterfaceRIPv2Enabled.name: cmIpInterfaceRIPv2Enabled
cmIpInterfaceRIPv2Enabled.description: This object allows to enable/disable RIPv2 on the IP Interface.

cmIpInterfaceDHCPClientIdEnabled.name: cmIpInterfaceDHCPClientIdEnabled
cmIpInterfaceDHCPClientIdEnabled.description: This object enables DHCP Option 61 on the IP interface. This object is only applicable when DHCP client is enabled.

cmIpInterfaceDHCPClientId.name: cmIpInterfaceDHCPClientId
cmIpInterfaceDHCPClientId.description: This object is applicable when cmIpInterfaceDHCPClientIdEnabled is set to TRUE. It allows users to specify the DHCP Client Id as a DisplayString - instead of the MAC address.

cmIpInterfaceIpMode.name: cmIpInterfaceIpMode
cmIpInterfaceIpMode.description: This object is the ipmode for the interface.

cmIpInterfaceDhcpClassIdEnabled.name: cmIpInterfaceDhcpClassIdEnabled
cmIpInterfaceDhcpClassIdEnabled.description: This object describe whether class id editable enabled.

cmIpInterfaceDhcpHostNameEnabled.name: cmIpInterfaceDhcpHostNameEnabled
cmIpInterfaceDhcpHostNameEnabled.description: This object describe whether host name editable enabled.

cmIpInterfaceDhcpHostName.name: cmIpInterfaceDhcpHostName
cmIpInterfaceDhcpHostName.description: This object describe the host name.

cmIpInterfaceDhcpLogServerEnabled.name: cmIpInterfaceDhcpLogServerEnabled
cmIpInterfaceDhcpLogServerEnabled.description: This object describe whether the dhcp log server enabled.

cmIpInterfaceDhcpNTPServerEnabled.name: cmIpInterfaceDhcpNTPServerEnabled
cmIpInterfaceDhcpNTPServerEnabled.description: This object describe whether the dhcp ntp server enabled.

cmIpInterfaceDhcpClientIdType.name: cmIpInterfaceDhcpClientIdType
cmIpInterfaceDhcpClientIdType.description: This object describe whether the dhcp cid type.

cmIpInterfaceDhcpHostNameType.name: cmIpInterfaceDhcpHostNameType
cmIpInterfaceDhcpHostNameType.description: This object describe whether the dhcp host name type.

cmIpInterfaceDhcpVendorInfoEnabled.name: cmIpInterfaceDhcpVendorInfoEnabled
cmIpInterfaceDhcpVendorInfoEnabled.description: This object means the vendor information whether enabled.

cmIpInterfaceDhcpVendorInfoType.name: cmIpInterfaceDhcpVendorInfoType
cmIpInterfaceDhcpVendorInfoType.description: This object describe whether the dhcp vendor information type.

cmIpInterfaceDhcpVendorInfo.name: cmIpInterfaceDhcpVendorInfo
cmIpInterfaceDhcpVendorInfo.description: This object describe the vendor information.

cmStaticRouteTable.name: cmStaticRouteTable
cmStaticRouteTable.description: This entity's user configured Static IP Routing table.

cmStaticRouteEntry.name: cmStaticRouteEntry
cmStaticRouteEntry.description: A particular route to a particular destina- tion, under a particular policy.

cmStaticRouteDest.name: cmStaticRouteDest
cmStaticRouteDest.description: The destination IP address of this route. This object may not take a Multicast (Class D) address value. Any assignment (implicit or otherwise) of an instance of this object to a value x must be rejected if the bitwise logical-AND of x with the value of the corresponding instance of the cmStaticRouteMask object is not equal to x.

cmStaticRouteMask.name: cmStaticRouteMask
cmStaticRouteMask.description: Indicate the mask to be logical-ANDed with the destination address before being compared to the value in the cmStaticRouteDest field. For those systems that do not support arbitrary subnet masks, an agent constructs the value of the cmStaticRouteMask by reference to the IP Ad- dress Class. Any assignment (implicit or otherwise) of an instance of this object to a value x must be rejected if the bitwise logical-AND of x with the value of the corresponding instance of the cmStaticRouteDest object is not equal to cmStaticRouteDest.

cmStaticRouteNextHop.name: cmStaticRouteNextHop
cmStaticRouteNextHop.description: On remote routes, the address of the next sys- tem en route; Otherwise, 0.0.0.0.

cmStaticRouteMetric.name: cmStaticRouteMetric
cmStaticRouteMetric.description: The primary routing metric for this route. The semantics of this metric are determined by the routing-protocol specified in the route's cmStaticRouteProto value. If this metric is not used, its value should be set to 1.

cmStaticRouteRowStatus.name: cmStaticRouteRowStatus
cmStaticRouteRowStatus.description: The row status variable, used according to row installation and removal conventions.

cmStaticRouteInterface.name: cmStaticRouteInterface
cmStaticRouteInterface.description: Name of the IP interface for the interface static route.

cmStaticRouteAdvertise.name: cmStaticRouteAdvertise
cmStaticRouteAdvertise.description: Whether this static route will be advertised via routing protocol.

cmARPTable.name: cmARPTable
cmARPTable.description: A list of ARP entries on the NIDs.

cmARPEntry.name: cmARPEntry
cmARPEntry.description: A conceptual row in the cmARPTable. Entries can be created/deleted in this table by management application action.

cmARPIndex.name: cmARPIndex
cmARPIndex.description: An integer index value used to uniquely identify this ARP Entry in the cmARPTable.

cmARPIPAddress.name: cmARPIPAddress
cmARPIPAddress.description: This object allows configuration of the ARP Entry IP Address.

cmARPMacAddress.name: cmARPMacAddress
cmARPMacAddress.description: This object allows management of the ARP Entry MAC Address.

cmARPInterface.name: cmARPInterface
cmARPInterface.description: This object allows management of the ARP Entry Interface.

cmARPStorageType.name: cmARPStorageType
cmARPStorageType.description: The type of storage configured for this entry.

cmARPRowStatus.name: cmARPRowStatus
cmARPRowStatus.description: The status of this row. The cmARPRowStatus object may be modified if the associated instance of this object is equal to active(1), notInService(2), or notReady(3).

cmARPEntryType.name: cmARPEntryType
cmARPEntryType.description: The type of ARP Entry. Note that static entries can be created.

cmProxyARPTable.name: cmProxyARPTable
cmProxyARPTable.description: A list of Proxy ARP entries on the NIDs. This table is not supported in GE206 Release 4.1CC.

cmProxyARPEntry.name: cmProxyARPEntry
cmProxyARPEntry.description: A conceptual row in the cmProxyARPTable. Entries can be created/deleted in this table by management application action.

cmProxyARPIndex.name: cmProxyARPIndex
cmProxyARPIndex.description: An integer index value used to uniquely identify this Proxy ARP Entry in the cmProxyARPTable.

cmProxyARPIPAddress.name: cmProxyARPIPAddress
cmProxyARPIPAddress.description: This object allows configuration of the ProxyARP Entry IP Address.

cmProxyARPSubnetMask.name: cmProxyARPSubnetMask
cmProxyARPSubnetMask.description: This object allows management of the Proxy ARP Entry Subnet Mask.

cmProxyARPInterface.name: cmProxyARPInterface
cmProxyARPInterface.description: This object allows management of the Proxy ARP Entry Interface.

cmProxyARPStorageType.name: cmProxyARPStorageType
cmProxyARPStorageType.description: The type of storage configured for this entry.

cmProxyARPRowStatus.name: cmProxyARPRowStatus
cmProxyARPRowStatus.description: The status of this row. The cmProxyARPRowStatus object may be modified if the associated instance of this object is equal to active(1), notInService(2), or notReady(3).

ipManagementTunnelTable.name: ipManagementTunnelTable
ipManagementTunnelTable.description: A list of IP Management Tunnel entries on the fsp150 family of products.

ipManagementTunnelEntry.name: ipManagementTunnelEntry
ipManagementTunnelEntry.description: A conceptual row in the ipManagementTunnelTable. Entries can be created/deleted in this table by management application action.

ipManagementTunnelIndex.name: ipManagementTunnelIndex
ipManagementTunnelIndex.description: A unique integer index value used to uniquely identify a Management Tunnel Entry in the ipManagementTunnelTable.

ipManagementTunnelAssociatedPort.name: ipManagementTunnelAssociatedPort
ipManagementTunnelAssociatedPort.description: This allows specification of the associated physical port on the device, to which the Management Tunnel is attached.

ipManagementTunnelName.name: ipManagementTunnelName
ipManagementTunnelName.description: This allows specification of a unique name which is also used as the name of the IP interface, to which the Management Tunnel is attached.

ipManagementTunnelType.name: ipManagementTunnelType
ipManagementTunnelType.description: This allows specification of the type of management tunnel, whether it is a VLAN based tunnel or a MAC based tunnel.

ipManagementTunnelMTU.name: ipManagementTunnelMTU
ipManagementTunnelMTU.description: This provides the MTU of the Management Tunnel.

ipManagementTunnelEncapsulationType.name: ipManagementTunnelEncapsulationType
ipManagementTunnelEncapsulationType.description: This allows specification of the encapsulation type of management tunnel. Only Ethernet encapsulation is currently supported.

ipManagementTunnelIpAddress.name: ipManagementTunnelIpAddress
ipManagementTunnelIpAddress.description: This object allows configuration of the Management Tunnel IP Address.

ipManagementTunnelSubnetMask.name: ipManagementTunnelSubnetMask
ipManagementTunnelSubnetMask.description: This object allows management of the Management Tunnel Subnet Mask.

ipManagementTunnelVlanId.name: ipManagementTunnelVlanId
ipManagementTunnelVlanId.description: This object allows specification of the VLAN Id in the case of a VLAN management tunnel. This object is not relevant for a MAC based management tunnel.

ipManagementTunnelSVlanEnabled.name: ipManagementTunnelSVlanEnabled
ipManagementTunnelSVlanEnabled.description: This object allows specification of whether or not the S-TAG is enabled on the IP Management Tunnel. This object is not relevant for a MAC based management tunnel.

ipManagementTunnelSVlanId.name: ipManagementTunnelSVlanId
ipManagementTunnelSVlanId.description: This object allows specification of the S-TAG VLAN Id in the case of a VLAN management tunnel, when S-TAG is also enabled. This object is not relevant for a MAC based management tunnel, as well as when the ipManagementTunnelSVlanEnabled is set to false.

ipManagementTunnelDhcpEnabled.name: ipManagementTunnelDhcpEnabled
ipManagementTunnelDhcpEnabled.description: This object allows specification of whether or not DHCP is enabled on the IP Management Tunnel.

ipManagementTunnelRip2PktsEnabled.name: ipManagementTunnelRip2PktsEnabled
ipManagementTunnelRip2PktsEnabled.description: This object allows specification of whether or not RIP2 is enabled on the IP Management Tunnel.

ipManagementTunnelPhysicalAddress.name: ipManagementTunnelPhysicalAddress
ipManagementTunnelPhysicalAddress.description: This object provides the physical address (MAC Address) associated with the IP Management Tunnel.

ipManagementTunnelCOS.name: ipManagementTunnelCOS
ipManagementTunnelCOS.description: This object allows specification of the Class of Service associated with the IP Management Tunnel. This value is also used in the p-bits of the VLAN based management tunnels (for both VLANs in case S-TAG is enabled).

ipManagementTunnelCIR.name: ipManagementTunnelCIR
ipManagementTunnelCIR.description: This object allows specification of the Management Tunnel CIR.

ipManagementTunnelEIR.name: ipManagementTunnelEIR
ipManagementTunnelEIR.description: This object allows specification of the Management Tunnel EIR.

ipManagementTunnelBufferSize.name: ipManagementTunnelBufferSize
ipManagementTunnelBufferSize.description: This object allows specification of the Management Tunnel Buffer Size.

ipManagementTunnelStorageType.name: ipManagementTunnelStorageType
ipManagementTunnelStorageType.description: The type of storage configured for this entry.

ipManagementTunnelRowStatus.name: ipManagementTunnelRowStatus
ipManagementTunnelRowStatus.description: The status of this row. The ipManagementTunnelRowStatus object may be modified if the associated instance of this object is equal to active(1), notInService(2), or notReady(3).

ipManagementTunnelDHCPClientIdEnabled.name: ipManagementTunnelDHCPClientIdEnabled
ipManagementTunnelDHCPClientIdEnabled.description: This object enables DHCP Option 61 on the Management Tunnel. This object is only applicable when DHCP client is enabled.

ipManagementTunnelDHCPClientId.name: ipManagementTunnelDHCPClientId
ipManagementTunnelDHCPClientId.description: This object is applicable when ipManagementTunnelDHCPClientIdEnabled is set to TRUE. It allows users to specify the DHCP Client Id as a DisplayString - instead of the MAC address.

ipManagementTunnelQosQueueProfile.name: ipManagementTunnelQosQueueProfile
ipManagementTunnelQosQueueProfile.description: This object identifies the OID of cmQosQueueProfileIndex in the cmQosQueueProfileTable.

ipManagementTunnelCVlanEnabled.name: ipManagementTunnelCVlanEnabled
ipManagementTunnelCVlanEnabled.description: This object CTAG whether enabled, By default it is enabled.

ipManagementTunnelDHCPv6Enabled.name: ipManagementTunnelDHCPv6Enabled
ipManagementTunnelDHCPv6Enabled.description: This object DHCPv6 whether enabled, By default it is enabled.

ipManagementTunnelIpv6Address.name: ipManagementTunnelIpv6Address
ipManagementTunnelIpv6Address.description: This object means the unicast ipv6 address.

ipManagementTunnelIpv6AddrPrefixLen.name: ipManagementTunnelIpv6AddrPrefixLen
ipManagementTunnelIpv6AddrPrefixLen.description: This object means the unicast ipv6 address prefix length.

ipManagementTunnelIpv6StateAddrAutoConfi.name: ipManagementTunnelIpv6StateAddrAutoConfigEnabled
ipManagementTunnelIpv6StateAddrAutoConfi.description: This object Ipv6StateAddrAutoConfig whether enabled, By default it is enabled.

ipManagementTunnellinkLocIpv6Addr.name: ipManagementTunnellinkLocIpv6Addr
ipManagementTunnellinkLocIpv6Addr.description: This object means the link local ipv6 address.

ipManagementTunnellinkLocIpv6AddrPrefixL.name: ipManagementTunnellinkLocIpv6AddrPrefixLen
ipManagementTunnellinkLocIpv6AddrPrefixL.description: This object means the link local ipv6 address prefix length.

ipManagementTunnelIpv6PrefixAdvertiseEna.name: ipManagementTunnelIpv6PrefixAdvertiseEnabled
ipManagementTunnelIpv6PrefixAdvertiseEna.description: This object means the prefix advertise whether enabled.

ipManagementTunnelIpv6Prefix.name: ipManagementTunnelIpv6Prefix
ipManagementTunnelIpv6Prefix.description: This object means the prefix ipv6 address.

ipManagementTunnelIpv6PrefixLen.name: ipManagementTunnelIpv6PrefixLen
ipManagementTunnelIpv6PrefixLen.description: This object means the link local ipv6 address prefix length.

ipManagementTunnelIpMode.name: ipManagementTunnelIpMode
ipManagementTunnelIpMode.description: This object means the ip mode for the management tunnel.

ipManagementTunnelIpv6RipngEnabled.name: ipManagementTunnelIpv6RipngEnabled
ipManagementTunnelIpv6RipngEnabled.description: This object means the ipv6's Ripng whether enabled.

ipManagementTunnelDhcpClassIdEnabled.name: ipManagementTunnelDhcpClassIdEnabled
ipManagementTunnelDhcpClassIdEnabled.description: This object means the class id whether enabled.

ipManagementTunnelDhcpHostNameEnabled.name: ipManagementTunnelDhcpHostNameEnabled
ipManagementTunnelDhcpHostNameEnabled.description: This object means the host name whether enabled.

ipManagementTunnelDhcpHostName.name: ipManagementTunnelDhcpHostName
ipManagementTunnelDhcpHostName.description: This object describe the host name.

ipManagementTunnelDhcpLogServerEnabled.name: ipManagementTunnelDhcpLogServerEnabled
ipManagementTunnelDhcpLogServerEnabled.description: This object describe whether the dhcp log server enabled.

ipManagementTunnelDhcpNTPServerEnabled.name: ipManagementTunnelDhcpNTPServerEnabled
ipManagementTunnelDhcpNTPServerEnabled.description: This object describe whether the dhcp ntp server enabled.

ipManagementTunnelDhcpClientIdType.name: ipManagementTunnelDhcpClientIdType
ipManagementTunnelDhcpClientIdType.description: This object describe whether the dhcp cid type.

ipManagementTunnelDhcpHostNameType.name: ipManagementTunnelDhcpHostNameType
ipManagementTunnelDhcpHostNameType.description: This object describe whether the dhcp host name type.

ipManagementTunnelDhcpVendorInfoEnabled.name: ipManagementTunnelDhcpVendorInfoEnabled
ipManagementTunnelDhcpVendorInfoEnabled.description: This object means the vendor information whether enabled.

ipManagementTunnelDhcpVendorInfoType.name: ipManagementTunnelDhcpVendorInfoType
ipManagementTunnelDhcpVendorInfoType.description: This object describe whether the dhcp vendor information type.

ipManagementTunnelDhcpVendorInfo.name: ipManagementTunnelDhcpVendorInfo
ipManagementTunnelDhcpVendorInfo.description: This object describe the vendor information.

cmIpv6InterfaceMTU.name: cmIpv6InterfaceMTU
cmIpv6InterfaceMTU.description: This object describe the MTU for ipv6 address interface.

cmIpv6UnicastAddr.name: cmIpv6UnicastAddr
cmIpv6UnicastAddr.description: This object describe IPv6 Unicast Address together with Prefix.

cmIpv6UnicastAddrPrefixLen.name: cmIpv6UnicastAddrPrefixLen
cmIpv6UnicastAddrPrefixLen.description: This object describe prefix length of unicast address.

cmIpv6PrefixAdvertiseEnabled.name: cmIpv6PrefixAdvertiseEnabled
cmIpv6PrefixAdvertiseEnabled.description: This object describe whether to advertise prefix to link in router mode.

cmIpv6RAPrefix.name: cmIpv6RAPrefix
cmIpv6RAPrefix.description: This object describe the IPv6 Prefix to be dispatched to link in Router mode.

cmIpv6RAPrefixLength.name: cmIpv6RAPrefixLength
cmIpv6RAPrefixLength.description: This object describe Length of RA prefix.

cmIpv6StateAddrAutoConfigEnabled.name: cmIpv6StateAddrAutoConfigEnabled
cmIpv6StateAddrAutoConfigEnabled.description: This object describe whether enable or disable stateless address auto configuration.

cmIpv6DhcpEnabled.name: cmIpv6DhcpEnabled
cmIpv6DhcpEnabled.description: This object describe whether dhcp is enabled on the ipv6 interface.

cmIpv6DhcpRole.name: cmIpv6DhcpRole
cmIpv6DhcpRole.description: This object describe the dhcp role.

cmIpv6RIPngEnabled.name: cmIpv6RIPngEnabled
cmIpv6RIPngEnabled.description: This object describe RIPng whether enabled.

cmIpv6LinkLocAddr.name: cmIpv6LinkLocAddr
cmIpv6LinkLocAddr.description: This object describe Automatically generated Link-local Address.

cmIpv6LinkLocAddrPrefixLen.name: cmIpv6LinkLocAddrPrefixLen
cmIpv6LinkLocAddrPrefixLen.description: This object describe Length of link local IPv6 address prefix.

cmIpv6StaticRouteTable.name: cmIpv6StaticRouteTable
cmIpv6StaticRouteTable.description: This entity's user configured Static Ipv6 Routing table.

cmIpv6StaticRouteEntry.name: cmIpv6StaticRouteEntry
cmIpv6StaticRouteEntry.description: A particular route to a particular destina- tion, under a particular policy.

cmIpv6StaticRouteDest.name: cmIpv6StaticRouteDest
cmIpv6StaticRouteDest.description: The destination Ipv6 address of this route. This object may not take a Multicast (Class D) address value. Any assignment (implicit or otherwise) of an instance of this object to a value x must be rejected if the bitwise logical-AND of x with the value of the corresponding instance of the cmIpv6StaticRouteMask object is not equal to x.

cmIpv6StaticRoutePrefixLen.name: cmIpv6StaticRoutePrefixLen
cmIpv6StaticRoutePrefixLen.description: Indicate the mask to be logical-ANDed with the destination address before being compared to the value in the cmIpv6StaticRouteDest field. For those systems that do not support arbitrary subnet masks, an agent constructs the value of the cmIpv6StaticRoutePrefixLen by reference to the IP Ad- dress Class. Any assignment (implicit or otherwise) of an instance of this object to a value x must be rejected if the bitwise logical-AND of x with the value of the corresponding instance of the cmIpv6StaticRouteDest object is not equal to cmIpv6StaticRouteDest.

cmIpv6StaticRouteNextHop.name: cmIpv6StaticRouteNextHop
cmIpv6StaticRouteNextHop.description: On remote routes, the address of the next sys- tem en route; Otherwise, 0.0.0.0.

cmIpv6StaticRouteMetric.name: cmIpv6StaticRouteMetric
cmIpv6StaticRouteMetric.description: The primary routing metric for this route. The semantics of this metric are determined by the routing-protocol specified in the route's cmIpv6StaticRouteProto value. If this metric is not used, its value should be set to 1.

cmIpv6StaticRouteRowStatus.name: cmIpv6StaticRouteRowStatus
cmIpv6StaticRouteRowStatus.description: The row status variable, used according to row installation and removal conventions.

cmIpv6StaticRouteInterface.name: cmIpv6StaticRouteInterface
cmIpv6StaticRouteInterface.description: Name of the Ipv6 interface for the interface static route.

cmIpv6StaticRouteAdvertise.name: cmIpv6StaticRouteAdvertise
cmIpv6StaticRouteAdvertise.description: Whether this static route will be advertised via routing protocol.

cmNDPTable.name: cmNDPTable
cmNDPTable.description: A list of NDP entries on the NIDs.

cmNDPEntry.name: cmNDPEntry
cmNDPEntry.description: A conceptual row in the cmNDPTable. Entries can be created/deleted in this table by management application action.

cmNDPIpv6Address.name: cmNDPIpv6Address
cmNDPIpv6Address.description: This object allows configuration of the NDP Entry IP Address.

cmNDPMacAddress.name: cmNDPMacAddress
cmNDPMacAddress.description: This object allows management of the NDP Entry MAC Address.

cmNDPInterface.name: cmNDPInterface
cmNDPInterface.description: This object allows management of the NDP Entry Interface.

cmNDPStorageType.name: cmNDPStorageType
cmNDPStorageType.description: The type of storage configured for this entry.

cmNDPRowStatus.name: cmNDPRowStatus
cmNDPRowStatus.description: The status of this row. The cmNDPRowStatus object may be modified if the associated instance of this object is equal to active(1), notInService(2), or notReady(3).

cmNDPEntryType.name: cmNDPEntryType
cmNDPEntryType.description: The type of NDP Entry. Note that static entries can be created.

cmProxyNDPTable.name: cmProxyNDPTable
cmProxyNDPTable.description: A list of Proxy NDP entries on the NIDs. This table is not supported in GE206 Release 4.1CC.

cmProxyNDPEntry.name: cmProxyNDPEntry
cmProxyNDPEntry.description: A conceptual row in the cmProxyNDPTable. Entries can be created/deleted in this table by management application action.

cmProxyNDPIpv6Address.name: cmProxyNDPIpv6Address
cmProxyNDPIpv6Address.description: This object allows configuration of the ProxyNDP Entry IP Address.

cmProxyNDPIpv6PrefixLen.name: cmProxyNDPIpv6PrefixLen
cmProxyNDPIpv6PrefixLen.description: This object allows management of the Proxy NDP Entry Subnet Mask.

cmProxyNDPInterface.name: cmProxyNDPInterface
cmProxyNDPInterface.description: This object allows management of the Proxy NDP Entry Interface.

cmProxyNDPStorageType.name: cmProxyNDPStorageType
cmProxyNDPStorageType.description: The type of storage configured for this entry.

cmProxyNDPRowStatus.name: cmProxyNDPRowStatus
